Preheat your oven to 200°C. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a 
#garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved).

In a #small bowl{}, add the garlic, half the lemon zest and juice, @oil for the chicken{},
@za'atar{1%tbsp} and plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Snip the string holding the @whole British chicken{1} legs together, remove and discard. 
Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{} and rub with the zesty zahtar oil.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Roast the chicken on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{60-75%minutes} depending on size.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when the juices from the thigh run clear and there is 
> no pink meat.

Meanwhile, bring a #large saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Peel and 
chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 4cm chunks.

Pour enough oil into a #deep baking tray{} to cover the bottom and pop in the oven.

Boil the potatoes for ~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges are soft.

When ready, drain in a #colander{} and sprinkle with @salt{} and the @plain flour{1%tbsp}. 
Shake to fluff up the potatoes, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray, turning in 
the oil.

Roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{45-50%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch}(roughly chopped). Trim the @chantenay carrots{150%g} 
and halve any large ones. Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved and deseeded), then finely chop.

In a #small saucepan{}, add the @pomegranate molasses{15%ml}, @red wine jus paste{22%g} and 
@water for the sauce{150%ml}.

Pop the pan on medium heat and bring to the boil, stirring continuously. Once boiling, lower 
the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the jus simmers, clean out the (now empty) #potato pan{} and pop on medium heat.

Melt in the @unsalted butter{30%g}, then add the carrots, @water for the veg{75%ml} and 
@sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Bring to the boil, then cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} and lower the heat. Simmer for 
~{10-12%minutes}, then remove the lid and add the @sugar snap peas{150%g}.

Cook until the liquid has evaporated and the veg is glazed, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring 
occasionally.

Once the potatoes are cooked, stir through the chilli (add less if you don't like heat), 
half the chives and remaining lemon zest. Cut the remaining lemon into wedges.

Stir the remaining chives into the glazed veg, then taste and season with salt and pepper if 
needed.

Reheat the veg and jus if necessary, then carve the chicken and share between your plates. 
Serve with the veg and roast potatoes alongside. Finish with the red wine jus. Enjoy!